Source package: scalable-cyrfonts

Binary packages: t1-cyrillic, t1-teams, t1-oldslavic,
                 and scalable-cyrfonts-tex.

Upstream packages:

    1) urw-fonts-1.0.7pre40-src.tar.bz2 from
       ftp://ftp.gnome.ru/fonts/
       Maintainer: Valek Filippov <frob@df.ru>

These fonts are included in t1-cyrillic and scalable-cyrfonts-tex.

    2) urw-fonts-1.0.7pre40.tar.bz2
       ftp://ftp.gnome.ru/fonts/
       Maintainer: Valek Filippov <frob@df.ru>

From this package we took only the documentation because it is not
included in urw-fonts-1.0.7pre40-src.tar.bz2.

    3) ftp://ftp.ice.ru/pub/fonts/type1/teams-1.1.tar.gz
       Maintainer: TopTeam Co. <http://www.topteam.bg>
		   Alexander Shopov <al_shopov@web.bg>

These fonts are included in t1-teams and scalable-cyrfonts-tex.

    4) oldslavic.tar.bz2 from 
       ftp://ftp.gnome.ru/fonts/
       Maintainer: Valek Filippov <frob@df.ru>

These fonts are included in t1-oldslavic and scalable-cyrfonts-tex.

License of the fonts in urw-fonts-1.0.7pre10-src.tar.bz2:

These fonts were made from the free URW fonts distributed with
ghostcript.  The license for result is the same as for the original
fonts, i.e. GPL with an exception that you can put these fonts in your
own non-GPLed documents.  On Debian GNU/Linux systems, the complete
text of the GNU General Public License can be found in
`/usr/share/common-licenses/GPL'.


